        "question": "How does feature flagging accelerate launch timelines?",
        "answer": "Feature flags decouple deployment from release they are the engineering practice that most directly accelerates launch timelines. Without feature flags: a feature cannot be deployed to production until it is 100% complete, tested, and approved for release any incomplete feature blocks the deployment of all other completed features. With feature flags: features can be deployed to production while disabled (dark deployment), then activated for a percentage of users when they are ready for release each feature ships independently, and the overall launch date is not held back by the slowest feature. The practical timeline acceleration: a sprint containing 3 features where feature A is complete, feature B needs 2 more days of work, and feature C has a minor bug can deploy features A and C at the end of the sprint (with C behind a flag not yet activated), address features B and C in days 1-3 of the next sprint, and activate C for users the sprint delivers two features to users instead of zero. ClickMasters integrates LaunchDarkly or Growthbook from sprint 1 of every engagement."
