        "question": "What is the difference between cost reduction and cost avoidance in software?",
        "answer": "Cost reduction is the elimination of a current, ongoing cost: replacing a manual process that currently costs $80,000/year with an automated process that costs $12,000/year to maintain. The $68,000 saving is realised each year after the investment. Cost avoidance is the prevention of a future cost that would otherwise be incurred: implementing security controls that prevent a data breach that would have cost $500,000 the $500,000 is not a current cost but a probabilistic future cost that the security investment prevents. Both have positive ROI, but cost reduction has a more visible impact on the income statement (the cost line decreases), while cost avoidance has a less visible but potentially larger impact (a prevented breach, a prevented compliance fine, a prevented production outage). ClickMasters quantifies both in every cost-focused engagement."
