        "question": "What causes software projects to launch late and how does ClickMasters prevent it?",
        "answer": "The four most common causes of launch delays and ClickMasters' prevention for each: scope creep (new features added during build that were not in the original scope prevention: a written scope document signed by the client before build begins, a formal change request process for any scope addition, and explicit communication of the timeline impact of every addition), external dependency delays (third-party API credentials, design assets, client approval not available when needed prevention: an external dependency log created in week 1 identifying every dependency, its owner, and the date it must be resolved, with weekly status updates), insufficient CI/CD (manual testing and deployment that cannot keep pace with development prevention: automated CI/CD from sprint 1, not from launch, so the deployment infrastructure is validated before it is needed at scale), and architecture rework (a design decision made in sprint 2 that turns out to be wrong in sprint 6, requiring 3 weeks of rework prevention: an architecture review in week 1 that identifies and resolves the highest-risk design decisions before development begins)."
