        "question": "What is the fastest realistic timeline to launch a software product?",
        "answer": "The fastest realistic launch timelines by product type: a landing page or marketing website (1-2 weeks), a Shopify e-commerce store with a custom theme (1-2 weeks), a web app with a single core workflow (6-8 weeks from scoping to production launch), a mobile app with the core feature set (8-12 weeks from scoping to App Store submission), a SaaS MVP with authentication, billing, and the core product workflow (10-14 weeks), and an enterprise software system with integrations and compliance requirements (16-24 weeks). These timelines assume: scope is fixed and not expanded during build, external dependencies (design assets, API credentials, third-party approvals) are resolved before development begins, and a dedicated engineering team works on the project continuously. ClickMasters provides a timeline estimate at the end of the scoping workshop before the contract is signed, so the client can evaluate whether the timeline meets their commercial need."
