        "question": "How do you calculate the ROI of software for cost reduction?",
        "answer": "Cost reduction ROI: identify the current process cost (hours per week x fully-loaded hourly cost x 52 weeks = annual process cost include staff time, error rework, and third-party service fees), estimate the automation or optimisation saving (typically 60-80% of manual process cost for business process automation, 20-60% of infrastructure cost for cloud optimisation), calculate the annual saving (current cost x saving percentage = annual saving), subtract the investment (ClickMasters fixed-price engagement cost + annual maintenance), and calculate the payback period (investment / annual saving = payback period in years). For a process costing $100,000/year, a $30,000 automation project saving 70% ($70,000/year) has a 5-month payback period. ClickMasters builds this ROI model with every cost-focused client before the project begins."
